						<summary>

						<p>On a pillar on the roadside about 7 miles from Mācherla.</p>						

						<p>Dated in Śaka 1056, <hi rend="italic">Ānanda, Pushya,</hi> solar eclipse, corresponding to A.D. 1135, January 16.</p>						

						<p>Gives a string of titles of a chief (name lost) and seems to refer to the installation of a <hi rend="italic">staṁ bha</hi> by him. (Cf. A.R. No. 216 of 1927).</p>						

						</summary>
